karengo
Homonym Number:
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:
Definition:<i>Porphyra columbina</i>, a common edible red seaweed [Maori], parengo (s. SI var. kareko).
Origin: Maori
Register:
Register 2:
Domain: [none]
Region: [none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: [Ma. <b>karengo</b> smooth, edible seaweed  (<i>Porphyra columbina</i>)] cf. P.M. Ryan Dict. Modern Maori (1995) 86.
