Date:  15/9/1987
Source:  Press, The
Author:
Vol / Page:  16
Edition:
Quote:  This is the genus Porphyra, varieties of which are found all over the world. in Wales it is known as laver (P. laciniata) in Japan as nori (P. tenera) while here in New Zealand we call it karengo (P. columbina.). Karengo looks like greenish purple sheets of cellophane with frilly edges, and is to be found clinging to rocks at low tide. in shape, it resembles green sea lettuce (Ulva lactuca) which is also edible.
